section.def:
autopsy
                (屍體剖驗) means an autopsy ordered to be performed
            under section 6(1);

coroner
                (死因裁判官) means a person appointed under
                section 3(1) to be a coroner;

discharge
                (履行), in relation to a duty, includes
            perform;

inquest
                (研訊) means an inquest into the death of a person
            held by a coroner, with or without a jury, under this Ordinance;

Registrar
                (司法常務官) means the Registrar of the High Court;
            (Amended 25 of 1998 s. 2)

paragraph.content:
the person was under the influence of a general anaesthetic at the time
                        of the death;
                        or

there is doubt as to whether the still born foetus was alive or dead at
                        the time of birth;
                        or
